&nbsp;
"Thank God there are also positive facts: I quote for example the ratification of the Agreement on the delimitation of the border between Tajikistan and Kyrgyzstan, which represents an excellent diplomatic result. I encourage both countries to continue on this road." Pope Francis said in the Angelus, whose text was only widespread.
<h2> Unemployed for South Sudan, short call for dialogue
"I follow with concern the situation in South Sudan>. I renew my appeal to all the Leaders, because they put the maximum commitment to lower the tension in the country." Thus Pope Francis in the text, only widespread, of the Angelus. "It is necessary to put aside differences and, with courage and responsibility, sit around a table and start a constructive dialogue," the Pontiff emphasised. "Only so it will be possible to alleviate the sufferings of the beloved South-Sudanese population and build a future of peace and stability," he adds.
"And in Sudan the war continues to reap innocent victims. I urge the parties in conflict to put in the first place the safeguard of the lives of their civil brothers; and I hope that new negotiations will begin as soon as possible, which will ensure a lasting solution to the crisis." He emphasized Pope Francis in the Angelus, whose text was only widespread. "The international community increases efforts to cope with the scary humanitarian catastrophe," is the Pope's call.
<h2> We live this Lent as a healing time </h2>
"We live this Lent, especially in the Jubilee, as a time of healing. I'm experimenting with it, in my soul and in my body. Therefore I cordially thank all those who, in the image of the Saviour, are for the next instruments of healing with their word and with their science, with affection and prayer." Pope Francis writes this in the text, only widespread, of the Angelus. "The fragility and disease are experiences that unite us all; to the greater reason, however, we are brothers in the salvation that Christ has given us," emphasizes the Pontiff.&nbsp;

